<title>USA: USG says to buy rest of Canadian firm. [CORRECTED 16:35 GMT 03/12]</title>
<headline>USG says to buy rest of Canadian firm. [CORRECTED 16:35 GMT 03/12]</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1996-10-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>USG Corp intends to make an C$11 per share offer to acquire the common shares of CGC Inc that USG does not already own, the companies said (corrects to Canadian dollars).</p>
<p>USG already owns about 76 percent of the Canadian gypsum wallboard company, the companies said.</p>
<p>The USG offer is a 60-percent premium over the C$6.90 (corrects) average  closing price of CGC common shares on the Toronto Stock Exchange over the  past 20 trading days, they said.</p>
<p>--Chicago Newsdesk 312-408-8787</p>
